File: The Health Department identified 772 new COVID-19 cases in South Africa. Pic: Marco Longari / AFP JOHANNESBURG - South Africa has recorded 210 new COVID-19 deaths. The Eastern Cape recorded the most deaths at 95, with the Western Cape following with 70. READ: Coronavirus in SA: Ramaphosa announces measures to curb second wave The death toll now stands at over 23,600. An additional 7,552 new COVID-19 cases have been recorded. Taking the total to over 873,000. Over 764,000 people have recovered.